Direct Known Subclasses:

public abstract class GridSerializableSet<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>
implements java.io.Serializable

Makes AbstractSet as Serializable and is useful for making anonymous serializable sets. It has no extra logic or state in addition to AbstractSet.

Note that methods AbstractCollection.contains(Object) and AbstractCollection.remove(Object) implemented in AbstractCollection fully iterate through collection so you need to make sure to override these methods if it's possible to create efficient implementations.
